    idealWorkflow:['Self-host on a $6/mo VPS (DigitalOcean or Hetzner) for full data control and near-unlimited executions','Use the AI Agent node to chain Claude or GPT-4o with tool calls (web search, database writes, email sends)','Add MCP server support to connect agents to any tool that exposes an MCP interface','Build error-handling branches on every workflow — n8n makes it easy to catch failures and retry automatically'],
    pitfalls:['Self-hosting requires server administration — updates, backups, and uptime are your responsibility','The cloud-hosted free trial is time-limited; the cloud Starter plan ($24/mo) has a 2,500 execution cap that fills quickly on busy workflows','Complex workflows with many branches can become visually overwhelming — good naming and documentation discipline is essential'],
