    idealWorkflow:['Use the web interface at midjourney.com for organized project management and visual exploration','Start with reference images (--sref) to anchor the visual direction, then iterate with style parameters','Use consistent character mode (--cref) for maintaining a character or person across multiple images','Inpaint specific regions to fix faces, hands, or backgrounds without regenerating the full image'],
    pitfalls:['The 200 fast-GPU images on the Basic plan ($10/mo) evaporate quickly during active creative work — most users need Standard ($30/mo)','Midjourney struggles with precise text rendering in images — use Canva AI or Adobe Firefly for type-heavy designs','Image consistency across a campaign requires careful use of style and character references; it\'s not automatic'],
